      "fieldOrBehavior": "New evals/integration/test_console_tenant_isolation.sh installs tenant-a and tenant-b via the REAL path (install-console-config.sh -> sourced config.sh -> transport.sh console_telemetry_emit) against a local Node HTTP stub; asserts each tenant's outbound POST carries only its own x-console-tenant-id + Bearer token, never the other tenant's (7 assertions x 3 checkpoints = 21 assertions, all pass). Re-run 3x consecutively with 0 flakiness (21/21 pass each run, exit 0). Fault-injected (set TOKEN_B=TOKEN_A) and confirmed the eval FAILS (6 checks fail, exit 1), proving it genuinely catches cross-tenant token leakage rather than trivially passing. Reverted; re-ran clean (21/21, exit 0).",
